Step 3: Wire the variable into the "Email - Action needed" body
Now replace the broken XPath expression in the email body with our new variable.

Click on Email - Action needed to expand it
In the Body field (in HTML mode), find this line:

@{join(xpath(xml(json(concat('{"r":', string(body('Get_CAPs_missing_BU')?['value']), '}'))), '//Title/text()'), '')}

Delete that entire line — including the @{...} wrapper
In its place, insert the variable as dynamic content:

Click where the line used to be
Open dynamic content picker
Find CAPRowsHTML under Variables → click to insert it
You should now see a dynamic content pill where the broken expression used to be



The <tbody> section of your table should now look like:
html<tbody>
  [CAPRowsHTML pill]
</tbody>

Save the flow

Reply "done" when the email body is updated.
